ZH: 我喜欢乘坐飞机飞行到不同的城市。
EN: I enjoy flying on airplanes to different cities.

ZH: 他是一名飞行员，每天都在飞机上工作。
EN: He is a pilot and works on airplanes every day.

ZH: 这个航班已经飞行了十个小时了。
EN: This flight has been flying for ten hours.

ZH: 我们飞行的高度是30000英尺。
EN: Our flying altitude is 30,000 feet.

ZH: 飞行员开始准备飞机起飞。
EN: The pilot starts preparing the airplane for takeoff.

ZH: 飞行员告诉乘客可以解开安全带了。
EN: The pilot tells the passengers they can unfasten their seat belts.

ZH: 飞行中要遵守所有的安全规定。
EN: All safety regulations must be followed during the flight.

ZH: 飞行员用无线电和控制塔进行通话。
EN: The pilot communicates with the control tower using the radio.

ZH: 飞机正在飞行途中遇到了气流颠簸。
EN: The airplane is experiencing turbulence during the flight.

ZH: 飞行员需要经过训练才能驾驶飞机。
EN: Pilots need to undergo training to be able to fly airplanes.

ZH: 飞行员掌握着飞机的操控技巧。
EN: The pilot has mastered the skills of controlling the airplane.

ZH: 飞机员正准备飞行计划。
EN: The aviator is preparing the flight plan.

ZH: 飞行员需要经常进行体检以确保健康状况。
EN: Pilots need to undergo regular medical checks to ensure their health.

ZH: 飞行员必须了解和遵守空中交通规则。
EN: Pilots must understand and comply with the air traffic regulations.

ZH: 飞行员必须牢记飞行指南中的各项事项。
EN: Pilots must memorize the various items in the flight manual.

ZH: 飞行任务需要仔细计划和准备。
EN: Flying missions require careful planning and preparation.

ZH: 飞行员必须具备应急处置能力。
EN: Pilots must have the ability to handle emergencies.

ZH: 飞行员必须对飞机的性能非常了解。
EN: Pilots must have a thorough understanding of the aircraft's performance.

ZH: 飞行员必须时刻保持警惕。
EN: Pilots must remain vigilant at all times.

ZH: 飞行员必须具备解决问题的能力。
EN: Pilots must have problem-solving skills.
